    Character Creation.
    
    1 – Choose a profession and race that match the setting of the game session.
    
    A profession is what constitutes the main occupation of your character.
    For example, paperboy, laborer, servant, revolutionary.
    Profession options may be provided by your GM (Gamemaster, game master).
    
    Choose one of the well-known intelligent races of the explored part of space:
    Human/Dwarf/Unathi/Slime Person/Diona/Vox.
    Other races and racial bonuses may be provided at the GM's discretion.
    
    2 – Determine your attribute modifiers.
    Attributes reflect the natural strengths and weaknesses of the character, and are represented by modifiers that will be added to the die roll.
    
    Modifiers: +3, +2, +1, 0, -1, -2
    Attributes: Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Wisdom, Charisma
    
    3 – Determine your character archetype.
    Like attributes, archetypes show what you're good at and what you're not, but in a more abstract form.
    As before, assign modifiers to the archetypes listed below.
    
    Modifiers: +3, +2, +1, 0, -1, -2
    Archetypes: Warrior, Rogue, Explorer, Sage, Artist, Diplomat
    
    4 – Grant yourself 10 determination points.
    Determination reflects a combination of physical and mental resilience, a character's will to exist.
    For more information on how determination works, see the "How to Play" section.
    
    5 – Come up with a name and determine your character's appearance.
    
    6 – Select basic equipment appropriate to your race and profession.
    
    Basic equipment is a set or collection of simple items or tools. For example, someone with an engineering profession might have a tool belt, fire extinguisher, and similar items.
    The appropriateness and scope of what items you can possess should be agreed upon with your GM.
    
    How to Play.
    
    1 – Start a quest.
    
    2 – To take any action, describe what you want to do, and then - only if the GM asks you - make a success check.
    
    Success Check = Результат броска 1d20 + Атрибут + Архетип в зависимости от класса сложности (5/10/15/20/25/30, на усмотрение ГМ).
    In case of failure, the GM may take a reaction against you (take an action or increase the difficulty of a repeat check).
    
    3 – If something attacks or otherwise acts against you, make a success check to defend yourself.
    
    4 – If you take damage, you lose 1 determination. If you deal damage, your target loses 1 determination.